# .vercelignore

# Environment files (Vercel uses its own env vars)
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# Logs
*.log

# OS files
.DS_Store

# Editor files
.vscode
.idea

# Documentation (except README)
*.md
!README.md

# Git files
.git
.gitignore

# Lock files (Vercel generates its own)
pnpm-lock.yaml
package-lock.json
yarn.lock

# Development scripts (keep if needed for builds)
# scripts/

# Database migrations (KEEP THESE - you need them!)
# migrations/

# Batch files (usually not needed)
*.bat

# Don't ignore node_modules - let Vercel handle it
# node_modules
```

## Key Changes:

1. **Removed `node_modules`** - Vercel installs dependencies automatically, you shouldn't ignore this in `.vercelignore`
2. **Commented out `scripts/`** - You need these if they contain setup or build scripts
3. **Commented out `migrations/`** - Your database migrations are essential for your app to work

## Better approach - Minimal `.vercelignore`:
```
# .vercelignore
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
*.log
.DS_Store
.vscode
.idea
.git